Title: Write an epilogue to a text adventure game story
Description: Given the storyline of the text adventure game so far, provide a fitting conclusion to the story
Input.Referring_Decision: You run away from officers.
Input.Story: The monarchy raids the rebel insurgent headquarters, capturing the leader. He declares war against all who oppose him with the threat of public execution. You believe in the rebels\' cause to liberate the people, but you are also afraid of being killed by the monarchy. You hear a banging at your door by someone who ends up being a high ranking officer in the monarchy. He immediately finds out that you are building weapons for the insurgents. You look around and see some soldiers of the monarchy walking towards you. You have noticed that on that first moment they were focused on seeking and capturing other rebels and none of them have realized the dead officer\'s body in front of you. THEN YOU MAKE CAVE INSIDE YOUR HOME TO HIDE OFFICER BODY.IT MAKES SOME NOICE. NOW DOOR KNOKING SOUND IS COME.YOU GO AND SEE WITHOUT OPEN DOOR BY WINDOW,ONE OFFICER IS THERE. After hiding the body you warn your family and they decide to flee the place, take what little they can and go to the depository where there are weapons and get a rifle to defend themselves on the way. There were 8-9 officers. They are ready to fight with you. They started following you. You all are very frightened. You run away from officers.
Answer.Story: Each one of you run in different directions, thus dividing officers into small numbers. With the weapons you carried, you and your family members not only defend yourself, but also kill all officers. All of you escape from there and head to the nearest forest to take shelter in insurgents' place.

Input.Referring_Decision: You run away
Input.Story: The monarchy raids the rebel insurgent headquarters, capturing the leader. He declares war against all who oppose him with the threat of public execution. You believe in the rebels\' cause to liberate the people, but you are also afraid of being killed by the monarchy. You hear a banging at your door by someone who ends up being a high ranking officer in the monarchy. He immediately finds out that you are building weapons for the insurgents. You look around and see some soldiers of the monarchy walking towards you. You have noticed that on that first moment they were focused on seeking and capturing other rebels and none of them have realized the dead officer\'s body in front of you. You find yourself in a forest, surrounded by dense and rather sinister looking trees. There is a path to your left and a path to your right. you will climb a giant tree to find a way into the deep forest. you see the little village of the tribe. They are growing vegetables and fruits like manioc, corn, beans, and bananas The people seem very friendly. They allow you to stay with them. After staying with them for a few days they are raided by the monarchy. You run away
Answer.Story: You don't want to put them at risk, but you agree that they will help you with food - this is very important for the rebels, they are threatened with hunger. You pick up as much as you can carry and go to the main rebel camp to feed and delight them. You keep on fighting.
